{"id": "736004", "revid": "22514", "url": "https://wowpedia.fandom.com/wiki?curid=736004", "title": "The Warden's Court", "text": ""}
{"id": "288078", "revid": "22514", "url": "https://wowpedia.fandom.com/wiki?curid=288078", "title": "The Warden's Game", "text": "Objectives.\nComplete the Warden's Game by teleporting the Warden's Pawns into inward-facing positions.\nDescription.\nYou see the statue split into two, then four, then eight identical statues in a square formation.\nYou hear a voice, not through your ears, but in the back of your mind:\nPerhaps this is a riddle of some sort?\nCompletion.\nThe jade statue becomes one again, and you place it in your pocket. You hear a shifting noise in the tomb's central chamber.\nNotes.\nThe game starts with all eight of the pieces facing outward and the objective is to have all the pieces facing inward. Pick an edge piece (e.g. the one on the north end) and click on it to teleport it to the center. Then click on the edge piece opposite the empty side (the southern piece in this example) and click it to move it across so it's facing inward (now on the north side), then click the middle piece to move it to the newly empty side so it too is facing inward (now on the south side). Then repeat the process for the other six pieces. Done properly, it only takes 12 clicks. Complete both games to be offered &lt;a href=\"Ancient%20Protectors\"&gt;Ancient Protectors&lt;/a&gt;."}
{"id": "115231", "revid": "49740203", "url": "https://wowpedia.fandom.com/wiki?curid=115231", "title": "The Warden's Key", "text": "The Warden's Key allows you to open &lt;a href=\"Captain%20Tyralius%27s%20Prison\"&gt;Captain Tyralius's Prison&lt;/a&gt; to release &lt;a href=\"Tyralius\"&gt;Tyralius&lt;/a&gt;.\nSource.\nThis item drops from &lt;a href=\"Warden%20Icoshock\"&gt;Warden Icoshock&lt;/a&gt; in &lt;a href=\"Netherstorm\"&gt;Netherstorm&lt;/a&gt;.\nThe Warden's Key as a quest objective.\nThis item is an objective of &lt;a href=\"Captain%20Tyralius%20%28quest%29\"&gt;Captain Tyralius (quest)&lt;/a&gt;."}
