{"id": "465679", "revid": "49740203", "url": "https://wowpedia.fandom.com/wiki?curid=465679", "title": "The Wardens", "text": "The Wardens are &lt;a href=\"Night%20elf\"&gt;night elven&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"warden\"&gt;warden&lt;/a&gt;s loyal to &lt;a href=\"Maiev%20Shadowsong\"&gt;Maiev Shadowsong&lt;/a&gt; operating in the &lt;a href=\"Broken%20Isles\"&gt;Broken Isles&lt;/a&gt;. They have worked from their base of operations, the &lt;a href=\"Isle%20of%20the%20Watchers\"&gt;Isle of the Watchers&lt;/a&gt; in &lt;a href=\"Azsuna\"&gt;Azsuna&lt;/a&gt;, to hunt down and neutralize major threats to &lt;a href=\"Azeroth\"&gt;Azeroth&lt;/a&gt;'s inhabitants, through imprisonment or summary execution. Captured foes were interned in the &lt;a href=\"Vault%20of%20the%20Wardens\"&gt;Vault of the Wardens&lt;/a&gt;. \nThey reward the heroes who help them deal with dangerous threats on the &lt;a href=\"Broken%20Isles\"&gt;Broken Isles&lt;/a&gt;. The faction is known to possess &lt;a href=\"Warden%20Towers\"&gt;Warden Towers&lt;/a&gt; across the Broken Isles, although in recent times they have been forced to abandon many of them. There are two in most \"Legion\" zones that serve as PvP targets.\nHistory.\nAt the outset of the &lt;a href=\"third%20invasion\"&gt;third invasion&lt;/a&gt; of Azeroth by the &lt;a href=\"Burning%20Legion\"&gt;Burning Legion&lt;/a&gt;, the &lt;a href=\"demon\"&gt;demon&lt;/a&gt;s targeted the Vault and, with the aid of the traitor warden &lt;a href=\"Cordana%20Felsong\"&gt;Cordana Felsong&lt;/a&gt;, they succeeded in overrunning the prison complex and retrieving the corpse of &lt;a href=\"Illidan%20Stormrage\"&gt;Illidan Stormrage&lt;/a&gt;. &lt;a href=\"Maiev%20Shadowsong\"&gt;Maiev Shadowsong&lt;/a&gt; was captured during the conflict and taken to &lt;a href=\"Black%20Rook%20Hold\"&gt;Black Rook Hold&lt;/a&gt;. The Wardens worked with the &lt;a href=\"Illidari\"&gt;Illidari&lt;/a&gt; to fight back the invading demons.\nIn Shadowsong's absence, took up the mantle of leadership. The Wardens continued their duties of upholding justice and safeguarding the world's inhabitants, directing &lt;a href=\"Adventurer\"&gt;order leaders&lt;/a&gt; to eliminate various threats on the &lt;a href=\"Broken%20Isles\"&gt;Broken Isles&lt;/a&gt;.\nIt is implied that the vast majority of the Wardens' ranks have been decimated by recent events, making it necessary for them to &lt;a href=\"Warden%20Trainee\"&gt;train new recruits&lt;/a&gt;, and to directly ask &lt;a href=\"adventurer\"&gt;adventurer&lt;/a&gt;s to hunt down prisoners who have escaped from the &lt;a href=\"Vault%20of%20the%20Wardens\"&gt;Vault of the Wardens&lt;/a&gt;.\nFollowing the creation of the &lt;a href=\"Armies%20of%20Legionfall\"&gt;Armies of Legionfall&lt;/a&gt;, members of the Wardens, including the now freed Maiev and several &lt;a href=\"Warden%20Vigilant\"&gt;Warden Vigilant&lt;/a&gt;s, participated in the &lt;a href=\"Assault%20on%20Broken%20Shore\"&gt;Assault on Broken Shore&lt;/a&gt;.\nReputation.\nFaction description.\n\"After Legion forces broke the Vault of the Wardens with the aid of , what few Wardens remain are determined to rebuild their prison and hunt down the terrifying beasts that were let loose when it fell.\""}
