{"id": "193427", "revid": "22514", "url": "https://wowpedia.fandom.com/wiki?curid=193427", "title": "The Stone That Started A Revolution", "text": "Objectives.\n&lt;a href=\"Crusade%20Architect%20Silas\"&gt;Crusade Architect Silas&lt;/a&gt; at the &lt;a href=\"Valley%20of%20Echoes\"&gt;Valley of Echoes&lt;/a&gt; in &lt;a href=\"Icecrown\"&gt;Icecrown&lt;/a&gt; wants you to retrieve 10 Trunks of Crystalline Heartwood and 10 pieces of Ancient Elven Masonry.\nDescription.\nYou may look at &lt;a href=\"Scourgeholme\"&gt;Scourgeholme&lt;/a&gt; now and see a rancid pit of decay, but one day it will be a place of glory and honor. &lt;a href=\"Tirion%20Fordring\"&gt;Highlord Fordring&lt;/a&gt; has deemed it \"Justice Keep.\"\nAlas, even an impregnable fortress like &lt;a href=\"Icecrown%20Citadel\"&gt;Icecrown Citadel&lt;/a&gt; began with but a single stone. So begins our search for the stone to start a revolution.\nTravel to &lt;a href=\"Crystalsong%20Forest\"&gt;Crystalsong&lt;/a&gt;, south of here, and seek out the &lt;a href=\"Unbound%20Thicket\"&gt;Unbound Thicket&lt;/a&gt; in the east. Once there gather crystalline heartwood from the thicket floor and elven masonry from the &lt;a href=\"Ruins%20of%20Shandaral\"&gt;Ruins of Shandaral&lt;/a&gt;. \nRewards.\nYou will be able to choose one of these rewards:\nProgress.\nAre you lost?\nCompletion.\nHeartwood by nature is resistant to disease, rot and plague. This heartwood, goes so far as to repel such things! The masonry, affected by the fallout of the Unbound Thicket, will work in much the same way.\nSoon we will break ground.\nNotes.\nDo this quest alongside &lt;a href=\"It%20Could%20Kill%20Us%20All\"&gt;It Could Kill Us All&lt;/a&gt;\nHeartwood litters the ground everywhere in the thicket. The masonry is blue and is only in the areas in and around the ruins."}
