{"id": "665736", "revid": "46586549", "url": "https://wowpedia.fandom.com/wiki?curid=665736", "title": "The Stonewright", "text": "The Stonewright is a &lt;a href=\"venthyr\"&gt;venthyr&lt;/a&gt;, the Harvester of &lt;a href=\"Wrath%20%28Revendreth%29\"&gt;Wrath&lt;/a&gt; of the &lt;a href=\"Court%20of%20Harvesters\"&gt;Court of Harvesters&lt;/a&gt;.\nShe is a former &lt;a href=\"Night%20Warrior\"&gt;Night Warrior&lt;/a&gt;, and the first venthyr created from a mortal soul, which was so long ago that &lt;a href=\"Prince%20Renathal\"&gt;Prince Renathal&lt;/a&gt; confused her with the &lt;a href=\"original%20Harvester%20of%20Wrath\"&gt;original Harvester of Wrath&lt;/a&gt; that was made alongside him and &lt;a href=\"The%20Curator%20%28venthyr%29\"&gt;the Curator&lt;/a&gt; from the will of &lt;a href=\"Denathrius\"&gt;Denathrius&lt;/a&gt; as the original Court of Harvesters. She refers to the &lt;a href=\"stoneborn\"&gt;stoneborn&lt;/a&gt; as her children and is referred to by &lt;a href=\"General%20Draven\"&gt;General Draven&lt;/a&gt; as the \"mother of stone\" and \"the mother of the stoneborn\", as she was the one who created the stoneborn and formed the &lt;a href=\"Stone%20Legion\"&gt;Stone Legion&lt;/a&gt; when the &lt;a href=\"Maldraxxi\"&gt;Maldraxxi&lt;/a&gt; forces did not come to defend Revendreth from the invasion of the &lt;a href=\"Light\"&gt;Light&lt;/a&gt; retaliating against the &lt;a href=\"nathrezim\"&gt;nathrezim&lt;/a&gt;. She personally banished the dreadlords from Revendreth due to the loss of her children.\nShe remained loyal to Denathrius during &lt;a href=\"Prince%20Renathal\"&gt;Prince Renathal&lt;/a&gt;'s rebellion, believing that he could not defeat both Denathrius and the Jailer and being unwilling to subject her children to the suffering of an unwinnable fight.\nAfter the defeat of Denathrius and the recovery of &lt;a href=\"The%20Primus\"&gt;The Primus&lt;/a&gt;, the latter sent a note to the Stonewright informing her of the return of the &lt;a href=\"nathrezim\"&gt;nathrezim&lt;/a&gt; and imploring her to take a side against the Jailer. Naturally, the Stonewright was wroth, and immediately set about removing the unseen guests from Revendreth and Sinfall. She and the Maw Walker uncovered a much larger nathrezim plot, and exposed &lt;a href=\"Mal%27Ganis\"&gt;Mal'Ganis&lt;/a&gt;. Later, she was beseeched by &lt;a href=\"Huln%20Highmountain\"&gt;Huln Highmountain&lt;/a&gt; who was looking for Night Warriors to aid &lt;a href=\"Tyrande\"&gt;Tyrande&lt;/a&gt; in &lt;a href=\"Ardenweald\"&gt;Ardenweald&lt;/a&gt;.\nQuotes.\nGossip.\nSo you are the one who slew the &lt;a href=\"stoneborn\"&gt;stoneborn&lt;/a&gt; outside of &lt;a href=\"Darkhaven\"&gt;Darkhaven&lt;/a&gt;.\nI am sure you did what you thought was right. Most people do.\nI am known as the Stonewright. By my hammer and chisel were crafted the first stoneborn, and I see each as my child. They are all brothers and sisters in arms, and now they wage war on each other in this short sighted rebellion.\nThe Master believes you can bring an end to this conflict. Of that I have no doubt. I only hope it is the right end.\nSinfall. This place holds barely a fraction of the power it once held.\nOne more reason to despise the dreadlords and their arrogant actions against the Light.\nI had fully expected Sire Denathrius to order me to smash this place into ruin along with you and the Prince still in it. He never did.\nThe relationship between Denathrius and Renathal is one not easily set aside by mere betrayal or attempted patricide, apparently.\nI am taking &lt;a href=\"Mal%27Ganis\"&gt;Mal'Ganis&lt;/a&gt; into custody and securing &lt;a href=\"Dominance%20Keep\"&gt;Dominance Keep&lt;/a&gt; from outsiders. You would do well to avoid that place for a time.\nI will bring my forces to bear on &lt;a href=\"Korthia\"&gt;Korthia&lt;/a&gt;, but it is still vital we extract as much information from Mal'Ganis as we can, and Renathal's methods are... soft... compared to mine.\nWhen I am done with him, Renathal can have Mal'Ganis back for whatever atonement he believes a dreadlord capable of. But not before I am done with him.\nHmm. I remember Renathal once tried to convince us to use the medallions to transfer the power of Revendreth to him alone.\nThis was long before the Master had revealed his true intentions. It would seem the &lt;a href=\"Maw\"&gt;Maw&lt;/a&gt;, and you, have done well to give our wayward prince some goals beyond his own success.\nWell done."}
