{"id": "526208", "revid": "27079649", "url": "https://wowpedia.fandom.com/wiki?curid=526208", "title": "The Storm Thieves", "text": "The Storm Thieves is a book by &lt;a href=\"Senior%20Historian%20Evelyna\"&gt;Senior Historian Evelyna&lt;/a&gt; that describes the history of &lt;a href=\"%3ATitanstrike\"&gt;:Titanstrike&lt;/a&gt;. The book's fourth chapter discusses how &lt;a href=\"Mimiron\"&gt;Mimiron&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Thorim\"&gt;Thorim&lt;/a&gt; imbued Titanstrike with lightning. Chapter eleven describes an &lt;a href=\"earthen\"&gt;earthen&lt;/a&gt; legend of when \"the sky went mad\" and thunder rolled through the heavens for weeks on end. &lt;a href=\"Loken\"&gt;Loken&lt;/a&gt; and several of his fellow &lt;a href=\"Keeper\"&gt;Keeper&lt;/a&gt;s followed the thunderous noise far to the south, where they discovered that the sky's unrest was caused by Thorim hunting &lt;a href=\"dinosaur\"&gt;scaled creatures&lt;/a&gt; with Titanstrike. Chapter twenty describes how the only beast to escape Thorim and his &lt;a href=\"Skoll\"&gt;two&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"Hati\"&gt;worgs&lt;/a&gt; on their hunts was a monstrous &lt;a href=\"jormungar\"&gt;jormungar&lt;/a&gt; worm, which the Keeper and his worgs pursued across the north for decades until the beast fled, never to be seen again."}
{"id": "180795", "revid": "27079649", "url": "https://wowpedia.fandom.com/wiki?curid=180795", "title": "The Stormbreaker", "text": "The Stormbreaker is a &lt;a href=\"destroyer\"&gt;destroyer&lt;/a&gt; docked inside &lt;a href=\"Valiance%20Keep\"&gt;Valiance Keep&lt;/a&gt; in the &lt;a href=\"Borean%20Tundra\"&gt;Borean Tundra&lt;/a&gt;. It acts as a stationary bridge between the northern and southern halves of the keep.\nThe ship made several trips between Valiance Keep and the &lt;a href=\"Eastern%20Kingdoms\"&gt;Eastern Kingdoms&lt;/a&gt;, delivering medical supplies to the &lt;a href=\"Valiance%20Expedition\"&gt;Valiance Expedition&lt;/a&gt;. Unbeknownst to the ship's captain, &lt;a href=\"Captain%20%22Lefty%22%20Lugsail\"&gt;\"Lefty\" Lugsail&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Cult%20of%20the%20Damned\"&gt;Cult of the Damned&lt;/a&gt; members from the mainland used the \"Stormbreaker\" and other Alliance ships to gain passage to Northrend. A &lt;a href=\"Cultist%20Shrine\"&gt;Cultist Shrine&lt;/a&gt; can be found below deck."}
