{"id": "88249", "revid": "40389549", "url": "https://wowpedia.fandom.com/wiki?curid=88249", "title": "The Tempest Key", "text": "The Tempest Key was the key to enter &lt;a href=\"Eye%20%28Tempest%20Keep%29\"&gt;the Eye&lt;/a&gt; of &lt;a href=\"Tempest%20Keep\"&gt;Tempest Keep&lt;/a&gt;, the inner sanctum of &lt;a href=\"Kael%27thas%20Sunstrider\"&gt;Kael'thas Sunstrider&lt;/a&gt;. The Tempest Key was not used like an actual key; instead, it was a passive item like the &lt;a href=\"Drakefire%20Amulet\"&gt;Drakefire Amulet&lt;/a&gt; that attuned the player to the instance.\nAfter it was removed as the key, players who completed the chain earned the title &lt;a href=\"Champion%20of%20the%20Naaru\"&gt;Champion of the Naaru&lt;/a&gt;. Even this option was removed with \"Wrath\".\nObtaining the Tempest Key.\nThe Tempest Key is given after a long quest chain that begins after completing &lt;a href=\"the%20Cipher%20of%20Damnation%20quest%20chain\"&gt;the Cipher of Damnation quest chain&lt;/a&gt; (starts with &lt;a href=\"The%20Hand%20of%20Gul%27dan%20%28quest%29\"&gt;The Hand of Gul'dan (quest)&lt;/a&gt;) for &lt;a href=\"The%20Cipher%20of%20Damnation\"&gt;The Cipher of Damnation&lt;/a&gt; in Shadowmoon Valley. Upon completing the Cipher quest, you will receive (immediately) a letter in the mail from &lt;a href=\"Khadgar\"&gt;Khadgar&lt;/a&gt;, asking you to travel to &lt;a href=\"Shattrath%20City\"&gt;Shattrath City&lt;/a&gt; to speak to him.\nUpon completing all four quests, A'dal will grant you the Tempest Key (along with &lt;a href=\"Phoenix-Fire%20Band\"&gt;Phoenix-Fire Band&lt;/a&gt;) and you will be allowed to enter &lt;a href=\"The%20Eye\"&gt;The Eye&lt;/a&gt;, Kael'thas' sanctum, for the final confrontation with the \"Sun King\".\nQuest progression.\nEither read the letter from &lt;a href=\"Khadgar\"&gt;Khadgar&lt;/a&gt; or speak to him in &lt;a href=\"Shattrath%20City\"&gt;Shattrath City&lt;/a&gt;.\nKeys required for quests.\nThe following Heroic entry keys are required, and you must be with a certain faction to obtain them:"}
{"id": "88250", "revid": "22514", "url": "https://wowpedia.fandom.com/wiki?curid=88250", "title": "The Tempest Key (quest)", "text": "This quest opens up after completing &lt;a href=\"the%20Cipher%20of%20Damnation%20quest%20chain\"&gt;the Cipher of Damnation quest chain&lt;/a&gt; in &lt;a href=\"Shadowmoon%20Valley\"&gt;Shadowmoon Valley&lt;/a&gt;. You will receive the &lt;a href=\"Letter%20from%20Shattrath\"&gt;Letter from Shattrath&lt;/a&gt; from &lt;a href=\"Khadgar\"&gt;Khadgar&lt;/a&gt; upon the completion of &lt;a href=\"The%20Cipher%20of%20Damnation%20%28quest%29\"&gt;The Cipher of Damnation (quest)&lt;/a&gt;, asking you to seek him out.\nObjectives.\nSpeak to A'dal in Shattrath City.\nDescription.\nYou have proven yourself capable of great feats, &lt;name&gt;. Your discovery of the Cipher of Damnation and Kael'Thas' involvement is most important to our cause. Should Kael use the cipher, what little is left of this world may collapse.\nA'dal is convinced that Kael must be stopped and now seeks adventurers willing to undergo trials. Those that prove their strength will be granted the Tempest Key.\n&lt;Khadgar nods.&gt;\nThe naaru's key to the vessel.\nA'dal awaits...\nCompletion.\nTempest Keep is a naaru creation, mortal. Access to the vessel has always been within our power to grant. A return to Tempest Keep, though, had been deemed unnecessary. A point of pride for a mortal race, perhaps, but naaru invest little in such things.\nWe go now because we must. Kael'Thas cannot be allowed to utter the words of damnation."}
