{"id": "345549", "revid": "49740203", "url": "https://wowpedia.fandom.com/wiki?curid=345549", "title": "The Ten Foot Pole", "text": "Objectives.\nHold back at least 10 s using the Ten Foot Pole.\nDescription.\nHere is a challenge for you: stand in the center of the room and hold off waves of monks using only a ten foot pole.\nMy record is ten. Can you beat that?\nRewards.\nYou will receive: \nProgress.\nIf there is one thing I've learned here it is that there is always more to learn.\nCompletion.\nAlright. You win this one. But next time I am sure I will do better.\nNotes.\nOn accept, a Ten Foot Pole spawns next to Lin. Interact with it. The rest of the NPCs all phase out as the adventurer is rooted to the center of the room. Monks will slowly start spawning at the steps walking toward the center. Merely click on them to repel them once they cross the blue dotted line, which is a 10-foot radius circle centered on the player. Any monks crossing the red dotted line (a 5-foot radius circle centered on the player) will attack and end the trial."}
