{"id": "674107", "revid": "39299307", "url": "https://wowpedia.fandom.com/wiki?curid=674107", "title": "The Third Fall of Kel'Thuzad", "text": "The Third Fall of Kel'Thuzad is the finale of the &lt;a href=\"%3ANecrolords%20Campaign\"&gt;:Necrolords Campaign&lt;/a&gt;, featuring the &lt;a href=\"%3ANecrolord%20Covenant\"&gt;:Necrolord Covenant&lt;/a&gt; attacking the &lt;a href=\"House%20of%20Rituals%20%28subzone%29\"&gt;House of Rituals&lt;/a&gt; to defeat their nemesis &lt;a href=\"Kel%27Thuzad\"&gt;Kel'Thuzad&lt;/a&gt; and rescue the captive &lt;a href=\"Margrave%20Sin%27dane\"&gt;Margrave Sin'dane&lt;/a&gt;. The quest mostly takes place in a single-player scenario titled Assault on the House of Rituals.\nThe &lt;a href=\"%3AVenthyr%20Campaign\"&gt;:Venthyr Campaign&lt;/a&gt; finale, &lt;a href=\"The%20Medallion%20of%20Dominion\"&gt;The Medallion of Dominion&lt;/a&gt;, depicts the same battle from the venthyr perspective.\nObjectives.\nRemove Kel'Thuzad from Maldraxxus.\nDescription.\nThe time has come to purge Maldraxxus of treachery.\nOur armies are rallied. Our allies stand ready. The machine of war is in motion.\nWe must win this battle, or all of the &lt;a href=\"Shadowlands\"&gt;Shadowlands&lt;/a&gt; will be lost.\nRewards.\nYou will receive:\nProgress.\nKel'Thuzad must be slain if we are to restore order to Maldraxxus.\nCompletion.\nKel'Thuzad escaped into &lt;a href=\"The%20Jailer\"&gt;the Banished One's&lt;/a&gt; hands, but at least his evil has been driven from Maldraxxus.\nWell fought, &lt;name&gt;. Now we focus on rebuilding our forces and restoring order to our realm.\nNotes.\nSpeak with Draka again:\nA cutscene plays:\nYou are then automatically placed in the scenario \"Assault on the House of Rituals\".\nStage 1: Into the Breach.\nYou start off placed some distance behind &lt;a href=\"Balmedar\"&gt;Balmedar&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Emeni\"&gt;Emeni&lt;/a&gt;, Draka, &lt;a href=\"Vashj\"&gt;Vashj&lt;/a&gt;, and &lt;a href=\"Alexandros%20Mograine\"&gt;Alexandros&lt;/a&gt;. Start running and the party will head up the steps.\nIf you run too far from the scenario area, the screen will fade to black and you'll get teleported back with the words:\nStage 2: Plan of Attack.\nAt the top, the Necrolord forces are already busy fighting Kel'Thuzad's minions. &lt;a href=\"Siege%20Artillery\"&gt;Siege Artillery&lt;/a&gt; is assaulting the walls while &lt;a href=\"Prime%20Steelskin\"&gt;Prime Steelskin&lt;/a&gt;s and &lt;a href=\"Mountain%20Watcher\"&gt;Mountain Watcher&lt;/a&gt;s are dueling &lt;a href=\"Necromancer%20Ritualist\"&gt;Necromancer Ritualist&lt;/a&gt;s. &lt;a href=\"Aran\"&gt;Aran&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Messana\"&gt;Messana&lt;/a&gt; are waiting by the side of the road, as is &lt;a href=\"Deathfang\"&gt;Deathfang&lt;/a&gt; (who can be petted). This scenario features a large number of &lt;a href=\"Lich%20%28The%20Third%20Fall%20of%20Kel%27Thuzad%29\"&gt;named lich mobs&lt;/a&gt; whose names are randomly chosen from \"Fel'endae\", \"Mal'endra\", \"Rathborne\", and \"Thultain\". Since there are only four possible names, there will oftentimes be multiple liches with the same name in each stage of the scenario. In this article, they will be referred to as just \"named liches\" for simplicity. In the second stage, two named liches are overseeing the battle from behind a barricade atop some stairs. \nWhen the player's party reaches the top, they are greeted by a huge projection of Kel'Thuzad.\nWhen you start heading to the stairs, the two Steelskins will automatically rush ahead, destroy the Barricades blocking the path, and start fighting their way up. A third Steelskin also spawns to accompany and assist you directly.\nThe stairs are guarded by two named liches, Necromancer Ritualists, and &lt;a href=\"Bone%20Thrall\"&gt;Bone Thrall&lt;/a&gt;s. At the top, Baroness Ninadar waits behind a wall of unattackable &lt;a href=\"Skeleton%20Bulwark\"&gt;Skeleton Bulwark&lt;/a&gt;s, continually raining frost magic down on the attackers. Help the two AI-controlled Steelskins clear a path to the top, at which point they'll instantly destroy the Skeleton Bulwarks, but Ninadar proceeds to freeze them in place. Aggro Ninadar with your third, as-of-yet unfrozen Steelskin companion:\nGet her to 10% and she teleports away:\nStage 3: Storm the Courtyard.\nDraka, Alexandros, Vashj, Balmedar, and two more Steelskins run up the stairs and into the &lt;a href=\"Grimoirium\"&gt;Grimoirium&lt;/a&gt; (labeled as just \"House of Rituals\" during the scenario).\nThe Grimoirium enters a phase in which it is filled with Ascended Liches, Necromancer Ritualists, and &lt;a href=\"Skeletal%20Defender\"&gt;Skeletal Defender&lt;/a&gt;s, many of which are fighting more Mountain Watchers and Steelskins. At the center of the area, an unattackable Ninadar is absorbing an immense amount of &lt;a href=\"anima\"&gt;anima&lt;/a&gt; from a huge crystal. To the southeast, down at the &lt;a href=\"Prime%20Arcanum\"&gt;Prime Arcanum&lt;/a&gt;, Kel'Thuzad and three named liches can be seen channeling around the &lt;a href=\"Ritual%20Bone%20Pile\"&gt;Ritual Bone Pile&lt;/a&gt; inside a circular wall of magic.\nKill the quota of enemies. Draka's party will help, but will not kill them on their own.\nStage 4: The Final Lesson of Baroness Ninadar.\nNinadar finishes her channeling and turns into Empowered Baroness Ninadar. Draka and Alexandros run over and start fighting her while Balmedar sits back and watches.\nJoin the fight. Ninadar will periodically cast Ice Fall, whose projectiles create ice blocks where they land, followed by casting Shattering Lance:\nAt 10% the encounter ends:\nStage 5: The Prime Arcanum.\nDraka, Alexandros, and Balmedar (now wielding the Staff of the Primus) join the Steelskins fighting around the area. The &lt;a href=\"Shield%20Stabilization%20Crystal\"&gt;Shield Stabilization Crystal&lt;/a&gt;s are guarded by two named liches. Defeat the guards, then interact with the crystals to destroy them. Destroying the first:\nThe second crystal starts a cutscene, advancing the stage.\nStage 6: The Prime Arcanum.\nA cutscene begins the stage:\nOn the other side of the cutscene:\nDraven and Kael'thas have now joined the Necrolords in battle at the stairs up to the &lt;a href=\"Reagentry\"&gt;Reagentry&lt;/a&gt; while &lt;a href=\"Sinfall%20Legionnaire\"&gt;Sinfall Legionnaire&lt;/a&gt;s roam the skies above. Kael forgets how to cast spells and tries to punch his way to victory while Draven stands by and watches. Aggro the giant, who is still standing in the center of the Prime Arcanum:\nYou are granted a bonus ability:\nWhen the ability is used:\nStay out of the telegraphs, use the bonus ability on cooldown, and take out the Infernous.\nStage 7: The Third Fall of Kel'Thuzad.\nDraven runs down into the Prime Arcanum:\nSpeak to Draven:\nDraven grabs you and flies you to the necropolis, &lt;a href=\"Exoramas\"&gt;Exoramas&lt;/a&gt;. Inside, Kael, Balmedar, Draka, Vashj, and Alexandros stand ready to face Kel'Thuzad, who is floating next to the incapacitated Margrave Sin'dane with the &lt;a href=\"%3AMedallion%20of%20Dominion\"&gt;:Medallion of Dominion&lt;/a&gt; on his chest. Rows of &lt;a href=\"Skeleton%20Bulwark\"&gt;Skeleton Bulwark&lt;/a&gt;s stand guard in Exoramas' four corners. When you arrive:\nThe battle begins. Kel'Thuzad becomes attackable and the party spreads out to attack the Skeleton Bulwarks\u2014Draven in the northwest corner, Kael and Balmedar in the northeast, Vashj in the southwest, and Draka and Alexandros in the southeast.\nThis encounter is an echo of the original &lt;a href=\"Kel%27Thuzad%20%28tactics%29\"&gt;Kel'Thuzad&lt;/a&gt; encounter in &lt;a href=\"Naxxramas\"&gt;Naxxramas&lt;/a&gt;. &lt;a href=\"Soldier%20of%20the%20Frozen%20Wastes%20%28Maldraxxus%29\"&gt;Soldiers of the Frozen Wastes&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Soul%20Weaver%20%28Maldraxxus%29\"&gt;Soul Weavers&lt;/a&gt; periodically spawn and fixate on the player. Take them out while working on Kel'Thuzad and avoid his variety of AoE attacks.\nAt 75% health:\nGet him to 10% and the encounter ends.\nFinal Stage: The Maldraxxian Armistice.\nA cutscene plays:\nAfterwards, the remaining party meets to discuss the future:\nUse the translocation sphere to get to the upper floor, where a Seat of the Primus portal awaits to take you back to Draka."}
