{"id": "365660", "revid": "39299307", "url": "https://wowpedia.fandom.com/wiki?curid=365660", "title": "The Thunder Forge (quest)", "text": "The Thunder Forge is the second step of Wrathion's &lt;a href=\"Patch%205.2\"&gt;Patch 5.2&lt;/a&gt; legendary quest chain. In order to complete this quest, players must have completed Wrathion's first step, &lt;a href=\"Secrets%20of%20the%20First%20Empire\"&gt;Secrets of the First Empire&lt;/a&gt; (20 secrets) and &lt;a href=\"I%20Need%20a%20Champion\"&gt;I Need a Champion&lt;/a&gt; (Wrathion exalted). Additionally, players must complete \"all\" of the &lt;a href=\"Isle%20of%20Thunder\"&gt;Isle of Thunder&lt;/a&gt; solo scenario quests up to and including &lt;a href=\"To%20the%20Skies%21%20%28quest%29\"&gt;To the Skies! (quest)&lt;/a&gt;\nThe majority of this quest takes place in a relatively difficult solo scenario, which can be started by speaking with Wrathion in the &lt;a href=\"Thunder%20Forges\"&gt;Thunder Forges&lt;/a&gt;.\nObjectives.\nProgress through the &lt;a href=\"Isle%20of%20Thunder\"&gt;Isle of Thunder&lt;/a&gt; until you unlock the &lt;a href=\"Thunder%20Forges\"&gt;Thunder Forge&lt;/a&gt;. Meet &lt;a href=\"Wrathion\"&gt;Wrathion&lt;/a&gt; outside the Thunder Forge and complete his task.\nDescription.\nEverything is prepared, &lt;name&gt;, and I have selected you to be my champion.\nNext, we must infiltrate the legendary Thunder Forge of &lt;a href=\"Lei%20Shen\"&gt;Lei Shen&lt;/a&gt; himself! You and your faction will need to advance forward until the Thunder Forge is exposed, if it isn't already.\nOnce you have infiltrated the forge, meet me there. Be ready for a fight!\nRewards.\nYou will receive: \nProgress.\nThe &lt;a href=\"Mogu\"&gt;Mogu&lt;/a&gt; will not appreciate my tinkering with their ancient forge. But we won't let that stop us, hmm?\nCompletion.\nBehold! The &lt;a href=\"Lightning%20Lance\"&gt;Lightning Lance&lt;/a&gt;! A conduit that can channel and control the very same power that the Thunder King used to found an empire.\nIt is dormant... but you're about to change that. If you're worthy.\nNotes.\nUnlocking the Thunder Forges takes place in the &lt;a href=\"Isle%20of%20Thunder%20storyline%23Take%20the%20Forge\"&gt;fourth stage&lt;/a&gt; of the &lt;a href=\"Isle%20of%20Thunder%20storyline\"&gt;Isle of Thunder storyline&lt;/a&gt;, after completing &lt;a href=\"To%20the%20Skies%21%20%28quest%29\"&gt;To the Skies! (quest)&lt;/a&gt;. Players must have completed To the Skies! and all previous solo scenarios in order to see Wrathion at the &lt;a href=\"Thunder%20Forges\"&gt;Thunder Forges&lt;/a&gt;.\nOn accept:\nAnduin follows up, depending on the faction:\nHead to the base of the stair between &lt;a href=\"Metal%20Lord%20Mono-Han\"&gt;Metal Lord Mono-Han&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Itoka\"&gt;Itoka&lt;/a&gt; at in the &lt;a href=\"Thunder%20Forges\"&gt;Thunder Forges&lt;/a&gt; and speak to Wrathion to begin the solo scenario \"The Thunder Forge\".\nAs in the Isle of Thunder storyline, this scenario can only be completed once, so it is documented here.\nStage 1: Speak with Wrathion.\nWalk forward a few yards to speak with Wrathion:\nStage 2: Forged from Trillium.\nGo to the nearby Mogu Crucible and click it to proceed.\nStage 3: Activate the Thunder Forge.\nAt the start of this stage three &lt;a href=\"Shado-Pan\"&gt;Shado-Pan&lt;/a&gt; appear, a &lt;a href=\"Shado-Pan%20Defender\"&gt;Shado-Pan Defender&lt;/a&gt; leading two Shado-Pan Warriors, jumping down from the wall along with the mogu.\nSeveral waves of mogu will appear as Wrathion charges up the device, occasionally the forge will send out a buff.\nWhen near its full charge:\nWhen the charge is at 100% &lt;a href=\"Forgemaster%20Vul%27kon\"&gt;Forgemaster Vul'kon&lt;/a&gt; appears:\nStage 4: Into the Forge.\nSpeak with Wrathion:\nStage 5: Corruption Detected.\nSha start appearing as a &lt;a href=\"Celestial%20Blacksmith\"&gt;Celestial Blacksmith&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Celestial%20Defender\"&gt;Celestial Defender&lt;/a&gt; appear.\nDuring the fight the Celestial Defender will drop healing lights announced with:\nThe Celestial Blacksmith will run between anvils will it becomes overcharged, while also being attacked by the sha. If killed the event will need to be reset.\nClicking the anvil will cause the smaller sha nearby to be destroyed and stunning the larger one. After several rounds of this, when the blacksmith is finally finished:\nFinal Stage: Manifested Corruption.\nThis fight will take some time, as the boss-level &lt;a href=\"Sha%20Amalgamation\"&gt;Sha Amalgamation&lt;/a&gt; has over 31 million health and the following abilities:\nThe Celestial Defender will again try to tank the amalgamation, but it occasionally gets banished with Dark Binding. The defender retains the green healing beam as well, but that may not be as useful with the area-denial abilities the amalgamation uses. It will either Shadow Burst when the player is within 10 yards, or Shadow Crash the player's position at range. Don't get hit by either. The amalgamation also unleashes a Meteor Storm that targets points on the ground indiscriminately, and also follows the player around. The amalgamation will also randomly summon a Debilitating Sha with 200,000 health that must be killed immediately.\nChampions who typically act as healers should focus on dispelling the defender and then worrying about doing damage.\nHowever, the most important move is Insanity. After a few-second wind-up, the amalgamation will channel Insanity for 60 seconds, which ticks for roughly 100,000 Shadow damage every second. This can only be prevented by using one of the seven overpowered anvils. Insanity is on a 30-second cooldown, and the boss \"will\" try to cast it as soon as it's off the cooldown. Each anvil can only be used once, so the champion and defender must get the amalgamation down to 20% health before the eighth Insanity cast kills the player. \nAt around 20% of total health remaining the lance will be ready to be used against the sha:\nThe lance spawns on the ground near Wrathion's position and is bathed in light. Interact with it, then quickly use the bonus action button to finish off the encounter:\nOn victory:\nSpeak with Wrathion to complete the quest. Complete this quest, then pick up the followup, &lt;a href=\"Spirit%20of%20the%20Storm%20Lord\"&gt;Spirit of the Storm Lord&lt;/a&gt;, before leaving the scenario."}
