{"id": "369314", "revid": "39381941", "url": "https://wowpedia.fandom.com/wiki?curid=369314", "title": "Knight (Warcraft I)", "text": "Knights are the fighting elite in &lt;a href=\"Llane%20Wrynn%20I\"&gt;his Majesty's&lt;/a&gt; service. Using the difficult skills required for mounted combat, these warriors wield huge &lt;a href=\"mace\"&gt;mace&lt;/a&gt;s in order to crush their opponent's skulls. Their &lt;a href=\"Horse\"&gt;warhorses&lt;/a&gt; make them fast and deadly, as they can maneuver much more quickly than an unmounted foe. Knights are well respected throughout the realm, and the tales of their fighting prowess are known far and wide.\nInformation.\nKnights are the main melee attacking unit. They are extremely useful as they have a good amount of HP and five points of armour. Their main usefulness is the fact that they are the fastest unit, and can also be upgraded to become even faster, making them useful in luring the enemy into a barrage of arrows. They are also very useful against &lt;a href=\"Catapult%20%28WC1%20Orc%29\"&gt;Catapults&lt;/a&gt; and spell casters; Catapults aren't able to hit a Knight due to the former's slow attack speed and a spell caster is only useful from afar."}
{"id": "429653", "revid": "6295293", "url": "https://wowpedia.fandom.com/wiki?curid=429653", "title": "Knight (Warcraft II)", "text": "The Knights of &lt;a href=\"Lordaeron\"&gt;Lordaeron&lt;/a&gt; represent the fiercest fighting force in the armies of the &lt;a href=\"Alliance%20of%20Lordaeron\"&gt;Alliance&lt;/a&gt;. Protected by suits of heavy armor, they carry mighty &lt;a href=\"Mace\"&gt;warhammers&lt;/a&gt; with which to crush all who would threaten the freedom of their lands. Astride great &lt;a href=\"Horse\"&gt;warhorses&lt;/a&gt;, these honorable and just warriors serve as a symbol of order to the peoples of Lordaeron in these dark and chaotic times. Having learned of the fate the &lt;a href=\"Brotherhood%20of%20the%20Horse\"&gt;Knights of Azeroth&lt;/a&gt; suffered after the &lt;a href=\"First%20War\"&gt;First War&lt;/a&gt;, they have sworn to both avenge their fallen brethren and free their homelands from the grip of the &lt;a href=\"Old%20Horde\"&gt;Orcish Hordes&lt;/a&gt;."}
{"id": "228011", "revid": "1487011", "url": "https://wowpedia.fandom.com/wiki?curid=228011", "title": "Knight (Warcraft III)", "text": "Though the hearty &lt;a href=\"Brotherhood%20of%20the%20Horse\"&gt;Knights of Azeroth&lt;/a&gt; were destroyed during the &lt;a href=\"First%20War\"&gt;First War&lt;/a&gt;, the shining Knights of &lt;a href=\"Lordaeron\"&gt;Lordaeron&lt;/a&gt; still continue to serve amongst the warriors of the &lt;a href=\"Alliance\"&gt;Alliance&lt;/a&gt;. These heavily armored warriors use mighty swords in combat which can damage enemy warriors up to several feet away. The Knights' speed and mobility mark them as the most versatile warriors of the Alliance. \nInformation.\nKnights are very powerful and fast troops, possessing high health, damage and attack. Be sure to research &lt;a href=\"%23Upgrades\"&gt;Animal War Training&lt;/a&gt; to increase their hit points. The &lt;a href=\"Paladin%20%28Warcraft%20III%29\"&gt;Paladin&lt;/a&gt;'s &lt;a href=\"Paladin%20%28Warcraft%20III%29%23Devotion%20Aura\"&gt;Devotion Aura&lt;/a&gt; is also good to use with Knights. Knights should also be accompanied by Priests so Inner Fire can further boost their impressive stats.\nMany Human players try to rush up to Knights as soon as they can to replace their &lt;a href=\"Footman%20%28Warcraft%20III%29\"&gt;Footmen&lt;/a&gt;. It is best to research the armor upgrades to give them even more armor. Knight usage is pretty straight forward; simply have them rush and surround the enemy before they can react.\nManual description.\nWading into combat astride their noble warhorses, the knights are renowned for cutting bloody swathes through enemy ranks."}
